
[1]immortality

   IMMORTAL'ITY, n. The quality of never ceasing to live or exist;
   exemption from death and annihilation; life destined to endure without
   end; as the immortality of the human soul.

   --Jesus Christ, who hath abolished death, and hath brought life and
   immortality to light through the gospel. 2 Tim.1.

   1. Exemption from oblivion.

   2. Perpetuity; existence not limited; as the immortality of a
   corporation.
